<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<ContentPage xmlns="http://xamarin.com/schemas/2014/forms"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="LearningApp.View.Module3Page" Title="Module 3">
    <ContentPage.Content>
        <ScrollView>
            <StackLayout>
                <StackLayout>
                    <Label Text="Module 1: Condition"
                           Padding="20,30,20,0"
                           FontSize="30"
                           VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand"
                           HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand" />
                </StackLayout>
                <StackLayout x:Name="ModuleCourseContent">
                        <Label 
                           Padding="20,20,10,10"
                           FontSize="Body"
                           VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand"
                           HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand">
                            <x:String>
                                Python supports the usual logical conditions from mathematics:
    Equals: a == b
    Not Equals: a != b
    Less than: a &#60; b
    Less than or equal to: a &#60;= b
    Greater than: a > b
    Greater than or equal to: a >= b
                            </x:String>
                        </Label>
                </StackLayout>
                <StackLayout Padding="20,0,20,10">
                    <WebView VerticalOptions="FillAndExpand"
                        HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand"
                        Source="https://www.youtube.com/embed/DZwmZ8Usvnk"
                        WidthRequest="500"
                        HeightRequest="200"
                        IsVisible="true"/>
                </StackLayout>
                 <StackLayout x:Name="ModuleCourseExample">
                        <Label 
                           Padding="20,10,10,10"
                           FontSize="Body"
                           VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand"
                           HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand">
                            <x:String>
Example:
a = 33
b = 200
if b > a:
    print("b is greater than a")

In this example we use two variables, a and b, which are used as part of the if statement to test whether b is greater than a. As a is 33, and b is 200, we know that 200 is greater than 33, and so we print to screen that "b is greater than a".
                            </x:String>
                        </Label>
                </StackLayout>
                <StackLayout x:Name="QuizButton">
                    <Button Text="Start Quiz"
                            CornerRadius="20"
                            Margin="20,0,20,10"
                            Clicked="redirectToQuiz" />
                </StackLayout>
            </StackLayout>
        </ScrollView>
    </ContentPage.Content>
</ContentPage>